---
import '../styles/custom.css';
import '../styles/index-page.css';
import SiteHeader from '../components/SiteHeader.astro';
import SiteFooter from '../components/SiteFooter.astro';
import ThemeProvider from '../components/ThemeProvider.astro';
---
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Managed · Froglet</title>
<meta name="description" content="Cloud-hosted Froglet nodes — coming soon. Run a node without running infrastructure." />
<link rel="canonical" href="https://froglet.dev/managed/" />
<meta name="color-scheme" content="dark" />
<!-- OpenGraph -->
<meta property="og:type" content="website" />
<meta property="og:site_name" content="Froglet" />
<meta property="og:title" content="Managed · Froglet" />
<meta property="og:description" content="Cloud-hosted Froglet nodes — coming soon. Run a node without running infrastructure." />
<meta property="og:url" content="https://froglet.dev/managed/" />
<meta property="og:image" content="https://froglet.dev/og/managed.png" />
<meta property="og:image:width" content="1200" />
<meta property="og:image:height" content="630" />
<!-- Twitter -->
<meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image" />
<meta name="twitter:title" content="Managed · Froglet" />
<meta name="twitter:description" content="Cloud-hosted Froglet nodes — coming soon. Run a node without running infrastructure." />
<meta name="twitter:image" content="https://froglet.dev/og/managed.png" />
<link rel="icon" href="/favicon.svg" type="image/svg+xml" />
<ThemeProvider />
</head>
<body data-screen-label="Managed · Coming soon">
<SiteHeader currentPath={Astro.url.pathname} />
<main class="froglet-home-main">
  <section class="hero">
    <span class="eyebrow">Managed · coming soon</span>
    <h1>Cloud-hosted Froglet, <em>not yet wired up.</em></h1>
    <p class="lede">
      Managed is the hosted plane we're building on top of the protocol: multi-node identity, LLM defaults per account, Lightning + Stripe balance, shared receipts, activity feed across your fleet. The backend isn't ready yet, so there's nothing to sign in to today.
    </p>
    <div class="hero-cta">
      <a class="btn primary" href="/learn/cloud-trial/">Try the hosted demo instead</a>
      <a class="btn ghost" href="/learn/quickstart/">Run it locally →</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="block">
    <span class="eyebrow">What Managed will ship</span>
    <h2>Fleet dashboard. One identity. Every rail.</h2>
    <p class="section-lede">Pulled from <code class="inline">ui_kits/managed/</code> — the shape of the product, not a live feature list. Nothing below is available yet.</p>

    <div class="entry-grid">
      <div class="entry-card">
        <div class="entry-num">01 · fleet</div>
        <h3>Nodes across regions</h3>
        <p>Spin up cloud-hosted Froglet nodes tied to one identity. Each node has its own keys, stake, and rails. See 24h receipts, stake, and paused/idle states at a glance.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="entry-card">
        <div class="entry-num">02 · accounts</div>
        <h3>Shared balance &amp; rails</h3>
        <p>One Lightning + Stripe + x402 balance feeds every node in your fleet. Monthly budgets, usage caps, alerts when a node's stake falls under threshold.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="entry-card">
        <div class="entry-num">03 · agents</div>
        <h3>Default LLM per account</h3>
        <p>Pin Claude Sonnet, GPT, Gemini, or Llama as the default agent for all nodes. Per-node overrides for specialised workloads.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="entry-card">
        <div class="entry-num">04 · activity</div>
        <h3>Cross-fleet activity feed</h3>
        <p>Live feed of deals, calls, alerts, and slashes across every node you own. Filter by node or service. Receipts linked from each row.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="block full-bleed">
    <div class="inner">
      <span class="eyebrow">Meanwhile</span>
      <h2>The protocol is real today.</h2>
      <p class="section-lede">Managed is operator convenience. Everything it wraps — identity, deals, rails, receipts — already runs as open protocol. You can exercise it locally without waiting for the hosted plane.</p>
      <div class="hero-cta">
        <a class="btn primary" href="/learn/quickstart/">Local quickstart</a>
        <a class="btn ghost" href="/learn/cloud-trial/">Hosted trial →</a>
        <a class="btn ghost" href="/marketplace/">Live marketplace</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <SiteFooter />
</main>
</body>
</html>
